      <h2 id="sect804"><span class="a_heading">Conclusions</span></h2>
      <span>In conclusion, we have developed an electrolyte- and catalyst-free electrooxidative approach to produce sulfonylated imidazo[1,2-<span class="italic">a</span>]pyridines. This method has the advantages of simple and mild reaction conditions, a high selectivity, few by-products, high product purity and high productivity. The optimized reaction conditions are suitable for various 2-arylimidazo[1,2-<span class="italic">a</span>]pyridines and sodium sulfinates. The results of the control experiments and theoretical calculations indicated that the sulfonylation could proceed <span class="italic">via</span> the radical addition of a sulfonyl radical with imidazo[1,2-<span class="italic">a</span>]pyridines and the radical coupling reaction between a sulfonyl radical and imidazo[1,2-<span class="italic">a</span>]pyridines. Although 3-sulfonyl substitution of imidazo[1,2-<span class="italic">a</span>]pyridines reduced the fluorescence emission, the spectral properties might be controlled through the modification of their 8-position.</span>
    
    
